import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'])
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    dirCat_counts = data['dirCat'].value_counts()
    dirCat_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Direction Categories')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of direction categories?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    direction_categories = data['dirCat'].unique()
    
    for category in direction_categories:
        subset = data[data['dirCat'] == category]
        plt.scatter(subset['dir'], subset['speed'], label=category)
    
    plt.xlabel('Direction')
    plt.ylabel('Speed')
    plt.legend(title='Direction Category')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of direction and speed for each direction category?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
